commentary.p:
First, we solve w=\frac{az+b}{cz+d}
    for z. This yields z=\frac{dw-b}{-cw+a}. When
    we check the composition, we see that

      \frac{a\left(\frac{dw-b}{-cw+a}\right)+b}{c\left(\frac{dw-b}{-cw+a}\right)+d}
	\amp = \frac{a(dw-b)+b(-cw+a)}{c(dw-b)+d(-cw+a)}

      \amp  = w\frac{ad-bc}{ad-bc}.


 Thus it is clear that the
    condition ad-bc is necessary and sufficient for invertibility.

Let Tz=\frac{az+b}{cz+d}
    and Sz=\frac{ez+f}{gz+h}. Then we have


	S(Tz)\amp = \frac{e\frac{az+b}{cz+d} +f}{g\frac{az+b}{cz+d}+h}

      \amp = \frac{e(az+b)+f(cz+d)}{g(az+b)+h(cz+d)}
      \amp = \frac{(ea+fc)z + (eb+fd)}{(ga+hc)z+(gb+hd)}
      \amp = \frac{rz+s}{tz+u}

    for r=ea+fc, s=eb+fd, t=ga+hc, u=gb+hd.
The composition is invertible
    because both of its factors are invertible. It follows from the
  previous exercise 
  that ru-ts\neq 0.

ol.li:
Let z_1,z_2,z_3 be three distinct points in \C. Verify that
	    Tz=\frac{z-z_2}{z-z_3}\frac{z_1-z_3}{z_1-z_2}
	    satisfies Tz_1=1,Tz_2=0,Tz_3=\infty.

statement.p:
Consequence of this exercise: We have the
	following explicit formulas for the cross ratio. 

      (z_0,z_1,z_2,z_3) \amp= \frac{z_0-z_2}{z_0-z_3}\frac{z_1-z_3}{z_1-z_2}

	  (z_0,\infty,z_2,z_3)\amp = \frac{z_0-z_2}{z_0-z_3}
	  (z_0,z_1,\infty,z_3)\amp =  \frac{z_1-z_3}{z_0-z_3}
	  (z_0,z_1,z_2,\infty)\amp =  \frac{z_0-z_2}{z_1-z_2}

ol.li:
Put together the pieces from the previous part.
[a\to 1, b\to 0,c\to \infty] \amp = \left[z\to \frac{z-b}{z-c}\frac{a-c}{a-b}\right] [1\to d, 0\to e,\infty\to f] \amp = \left[z\to \frac{f(e-d)z +e(d-f)}{(e-d)z+d-f} \right]
[a\to d,b\to e,c\to f] \amp = [1\to d, 0\to e,\infty\to f]\circ [a\to 1, b\to 0,c\to \infty]
\amp \leftrightarrow \twotwo{f(e-d)}{e(d-f)}{e-d}{d-f}\twotwo{a-c}{b(c-a)}{a-b}{c(b-a)}
\amp \leftrightarrow \twotwo{ef(b-c)+df(c-a)+ed(a-b)}{abf(d-e)+bcd(e-f) +ace(f-d)}{d(c-b)+e(a-c)+f(b-a)}{ab(d-e)+bc(e-f)+ac(f-d)}

This is similar to ii above. Equality (1) uses invariance of the cross ratio, applying the Möbius transformation
u\amp \to a^\ast u \amp \to a^\ast u + b^\ast -b \amp \to \frac{a^\ast u + b^\ast -b}{a}
to all four entries in the cross ratio immediately preceding the equals sign labeled (1).

statement.p:
	Find the normal form and sketch a graph using Steiner circles
	for the following transformations.

z\to \frac{1}{z}


	    z\to \frac{3z-1}{z+1}

commentary.p:
We have

      S\amp \leftrightarrow \twotwo{0}{1}{1}{-p}
      S^{-1}\amp \leftrightarrow \twotwo{-p}{-1}{-1}{0}\sim \twotwo{p}{1}{1}{0}      

    so S^{-1}w=\frac{pw+1}{w}, so S^{-1}
	takes 0,\beta,\infty
    to \infty,\frac{p\beta+1}{\beta},p. Thus, S^{-1}
    transforms the line through 0,\beta in the w-plane to
    the line through \frac{p\beta+1}{\beta},p in
	the z-plane. This degenerate Steiner line has a direction
    vector given
	by \frac{p\beta+1}{\beta}-p=\frac{p\beta+1-p\beta}{\beta}
	=\frac{1}{\beta} = \frac{\beta^\ast}{|\beta|^2}\propto
	\beta^\ast, as claimed.
